-MS\nbrown dwarfs in the Association may have survived because their X-ray\nluminosities and, hence, disk photoevaporation rates are very low to begin\nwith, and then further decline relatively early in their pre-MS evolution.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 30 Mar 2016 18:48:24 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-06-22"}
